In Eq. (2), N(x,t) represents the modeled tumor cellularity at position x and time t, D is the diffusivity coefficient, k(x) is a spatially resolved proliferation map and γj is a spatio-temporally resolved function describing the effects of the jth chemotherapy drug (where j ∈ [A, C], where “A” and “C” denote Adriamycin and Cytoxan, respectively). This treatment function is defined by Eq. (3):3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
